@maydaygmail If you want faster convergence, you can try 

python toy_ctc.py

It will converge faster than lstm_ocr.py

I think it is due to something incompatible with the linked native libs.
The core/Base is coded to try NativeLibraryLoader automatically, which will look for .so in the assembly jar. The error printed here does not explain the real reason. I'll fix this log problem.

Please temporally apply the following patch to find out the real issue:

```
diff --git a/scala-package/core/src/main/scala/ml/dmlc/mxnet/Base.scala b/scala-package/core/src/main/scala/ml/dmlc/mxnet/Base.scala
index d995176..bc910f4 100644
--- a/scala-package/core/src/main/scala/ml/dmlc/mxnet/Base.scala
+++ b/scala-package/core/src/main/scala/ml/dmlc/mxnet/Base.scala
@@ -35,6 +35,8 @@ object Base {
   type SymbolHandleRef = RefLong

   try {
+    tryLoadLibraryOS("mxnet-scala")
+    /*
     try {
       tryLoadLibraryOS("mxnet-scala")
     } catch {
@@ -46,6 +48,7 @@ object Base {
           "or specifying by Java cmd option -Djava.library.path=[lib path].")
         NativeLibraryLoader.loadLibrary("mxnet-scala")
     }
+    */
   } catch {
     case e: UnsatisfiedLinkError =>
       logger.error("Couldn't find native library mxnet-scala")
```

